# Routing + Structure

## Structure (preferred)

- `src/app.(js|ts)`: app wiring (middleware/routes)
- `src/server.(js|ts)`: listen/startup only
- `src/routes/`: route definitions only
- `src/handlers/`: HTTP-specific logic (req/res), no DB calls directly
- `src/services/`: business logic
- `src/data/`: repositories/queries
- `src/middlewares/`: auth, validation, error handling

## Route rules

- Routes should be **thin**: map method+path to a handler.
- Handlers should not know storage details; call a service.
- Use a **router per resource** (e.g., `users.routes`).
- Name handlers as `createX`, `getX`, `listX`, `updateX`, `deleteX`.
